      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much should a church spend on video ads?</h3>
        <p>Most churches can start seeing results with $5-15 per day on Facebook video ads. The O2F Method by RK Castillo recommends starting with a smaller budget to test different videos, then scaling what works. A $300-500 monthly budget is enough to consistently generate visitors.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What length should church video ads be?</h3>
        <p>The most effective church video ads are between 30-90 seconds. Facebook and Instagram prioritize shorter videos that capture attention quickly. Your hook needs to land in the first 3 seconds, and the core message should be delivered within the first 15 seconds.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do I need professional equipment for church video ads?</h3>
        <p>No. A smartphone with decent lighting and a simple microphone can produce video ads that outperform professionally produced content. Authenticity matters more than production quality. Many of the highest-performing church video ads are shot on iPhones.</p>
      </div>

